28. To answer the above question, the Court has to consider the following:
(a) whether the appellants were aware of the ex parte interim order;
(b) whether the appellants were bound by the ex parte interim order and;
Discussion on the question (a):
29.

On reading XXXIX Rule 2A (1) of the Code, it is evident that the Rule provides for;
(a) attachment of the property of the wrongdoer,
(b) civil imprisonment not exceeding three months.
